[2]
Date: Mon 27 Feb 2006
From: T Jacob John <vlr_tjjohn@sancharnet.in>

Comment from Professor T Jacob John
-----------------------------------
This comment refers to the ProMED-mail report of 27 Feb 2006 on an outbreak
of fever with severe limb pain and joint swelling in Karnataka State in
southern India [see: Undiagnosed disease - India (Karnakata): RFI
20060227.0635]. The clinical picture sounds very much like Chikungunya
virus disease.
On 20 Feb 2006, ProMED-mail had reported on Chikungunya in Andhra Pradesh
State, which is adjacent to Karnataka [see: Chikungunya - India (AP): susp.
20060220.0551]. On 30 Jan 2006, I saw one patient with typical
Chikungunya-like illness from which he had recovered, but who continued to
have swelling of the feet and large-joint pain going on for several days
after recovery from fever. That was in Hyderabad, capital city of Andhra
Pradesh State. I would strongly suggest Chikungunya in Karnataka also, but
virological studies are necessary to check this out.
--
T Jacob John
Formerly (Retired) Professor & Head of the Department of Clinical Virology
Christian Medical College & Hospital
Vellore, Tamil Nadu, 632 002
India
<vlr_tjjohn@sancharnet.in>
